The article is a transcript of a speech given by Vice President Mike Pence in Charlotte, North Carolina. Pence thanks the audience for their support and brings greetings from President Donald Trump. He discusses various promises made by the President and the accomplishments of the administration, including tax cuts, rebuilding the military, securing the borders, and appointing conservative judges. Pence emphasizes the positive impact of the tax cuts on the economy and job creation. He also encourages the audience to stay informed, get involved, and share the achievements of the administration with others. Pence concludes by urging the audience to pray for America and express confidence in the future of the country.